{"id":704,"date":"2011-02-16T10:34:45","date_gmt":"2011-02-16T10:34:45","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/joind.co.uk\/?p=704"},"modified":"2017-02-11T08:16:09","modified_gmt":"2017-02-11T08:16:09","slug":"spirituality-blogging","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/joind.co.uk\/spirituality-blogging\/","title":{"rendered":"&#8220;Spirituality&#8221; slows down blogging"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>\u201cSpirituality is when the inside of things is bigger than the outside\u201d &#8211; Richard Rohr.<\/p>\n<p>I came across that quote while I was taking a look at the new website of\u00a0 <a href=\"http:\/\/www.saint-saviour.org\/\">St Saviour&#8217;s, Bridge of Allan<\/a> where my brother is rector.<!--more--><\/p>\n<p>It just happened to catch my eye because I was about to write a post on why I was finding it hard to post at the moment.<\/p>\n<h3>Why it&#8217;s sometimes hard to write a blog post<\/h3>\n<p>There are many times in life when I find my inner world more vivid and enticing than the outer world: I can&#8217;t read on the bus because I want to stare out of the window, I&#8217;m late for an appointment because I have been day-dreaming in the bath, I don&#8217;t switch the telly on because lying on my back looking at the ceiling is far more entertaining than anything being offered to me on a screen.<\/p>\n<p>I&#8217;m going through a time like this at the moment &#8211; a time when I am being beckoned by my soul rather than wooed through the web. The outer world is small and thin. My inner world is rich and deep.<\/p>\n<p>I don&#8217;t know if this is &#8220;spirituality.&#8221;\u00a0 I don&#8217;t know if this is the way of being to which Richard Rohr was alluding. But it is good to name this place and it a good place to be.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>\u201cSpirituality is when the inside of things is bigger than the outside\u201d &#8211; Richard Rohr. I came across that quote while I was taking a look at the new website of\u